[[File:Mongolia - electric power production.png|thumb|Electricity production in Mongolia in 1960-2010]]
The '''electricity sector in Mongolia''' ranges from [[Electricity generation|generation]], [[Electric power transmission|transmission]], [[Electric power distribution|distribution]] and [[Electricity market|sales]] of electricity in [[Mongolia]].
==Generation==
===Power plant types=== [[File:Power plant near Ulaanbaatar.jpg|thumb|Power plant near [[Ulan Bator]]]] [[File:Solar panels in Ogiinuur.jpg|thumb|[[Solar panel]] in [[Ögii nuur, Arkhangai|Ögii nuur]], [[Arkhangai Province]]]]
In 2010, the total amount of electricity produced by all types of power plant in Mongolia are 4,256.1 GWh (thermal power), 31 GWh (hydroelectric), 13.2 GWh (diesel) and 0.6 GWh (solar and wind).<ref>http://jref.or.jp/images/pdf/20120309/9March_REvision2012_keynote_tsagaan.pdf</ref>
===Fuel types=== In 2012, [[coal]] is used to generate 98% of the electricity in Mongolia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldcoal.org/resources/coal-statistics/ |title=Coal Facts &#124; WCA &#124; World Coal Association |publisher=Worldcoal.org |date= |accessdate=2014-04-21}}</ref>
