{{coord|37|43|52.08|N|122|12|24.18|W|region:US|display=title}}
{{Infobox park | name = Martin Luther King Jr. Regional Shoreline | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | map = <!-- or | map_image = --> | map_width = | type = Regional Shoreline | location = San Francisco Bay Area | nearest_city = Oakland, California | coordinates = | area = {{741|acres|ha}} | created = 1993 | operator = East Bay Regional Parks | visitation_num = | status = Open | designation = | open = }} '''Martin Luther King Jr. Shoreline''' is a [[regional park]] located on the shores of the [[San Leandro Bay]] in [[Oakland, California]]. Part of the [[East Bay Regional Park District|East Bay Regional Parks]] system, it is named after [[Civil Rights Movement]] leader [[Martin Luther King Jr.]] The park was established in 1993 on a {{convert|741|acre|ha}} tract of land leased from the Oakland Airport.<ref name="EBRP-MLKRS">[http://www.ebparks.org/parks/martinlking "Martin Luther King Jr. Regional Shoreline." East Bay Regional Parks system.] Accessed July 14, 2018.</ref>
==Facilities== * The Shoreline Center is an indoor-outdoor venue that is available for parties, weddings, corporate, school and other group events. It contains a main room, an outdoor deck and a commercial kitchen. Catering can be provided. The facility is rated for 60 guests (seated) or 125 (standing).<ref name="EBRP-MLKRS"/>
* The Tidewater Boating Center is a complex that includes an ADA-accessible dock, a boat house and boat storage area, training area, Recreation Department offices and a security residence. The area of the complex is {{convert|12300|ft2|m2}}.<ref name="EBRP-MLKRS"/>
