'''Molybdenum carbide''' ([[Molybdenum|Mo]][[Carbon|C]] and Mo<sub>2</sub>C) is an extremely [[hardness|hard]] [[refraction (metallurgy)|refractory]] [[ceramic]] material, commercially used in [[tool bit]]s for cutting tools.

