{{Infobox power station | name = Borkum West II | location_map = Germany | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|54|02|30|N|6|28|0|E|region:DE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Germany | location = 45&nbsp;km North of Borkum island | status = O | construction_began = September 2011 | commissioned = {{Start date|2015|July}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enerdata.net/enerdatauk/press-and-publication/energy-news-001/200-mw-borkum-offshore-wind-park-comes-stream-germany_33419.html | title = Borkum West II Commissioned | publisher = Enerdata | accessdate=20 July 2015}}</ref> | decommissioned = | cost = EUR900m (Phase 1) ? (Phase 2) | owner = Trianel + 33 municipal utilities | operator = Trianel | ps_units_operational = 40 x 5&nbsp;MW | ps_units_planned = 32 x 6.34&nbsp;MW<ref name=trianel2/> | ps_units_manu_model = [[Areva Wind]] M5000-116<ref name=trianel/> | wind_hub_height = | wind_rotor_diameter = 116&nbsp;m | wind_rated_speed = | wind_farm_type = offshore | wind_site_elevation = | wind_site_usage = | wind_site_area = | wind_offshore_depth = 33&nbsp;m | wind_offshore_distance = 45&nbsp;km (65.6&nbsp;km for center) | ps_electrical_capacity = 200 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = {{URL|http://www.trianel-borkum.de/en/start.html}} | extra = }} [[File:Karte Offshore-Windkraftanlagen in der Deutschen Bucht.png|thumb|Borkum West II's location in the wind farms of the German Bight]]
'''Trianel Windpark Borkum''' (formerly '''Borkum West II''') is an offshore wind farm near [[Borkum]]. Its first phase of 40 turbines rated at a total power of 200&nbsp;MW is operational, with a planned, additional 200&nbsp;MW in a second phase.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.power-technology.com/projects/borkum-farm/ | title = Borkum West II Offshore Wind Farm, Germany | publisher = power-technology.com | accessdate = 24 January 2013}}{{Unreliable source?|reason=domain on WP:BLACKLIST|date=June 2016}}</ref> The project was approved for construction in 2008<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Berkenhagen | first1 = J. R. | last2 = Döring | first2 = R. | last3 = Fock | first3 = H. O. | last4 = Kloppmann | first4 = M. H. F. | last5 = Pedersen | first5 = S. R. A. | last6 = Schulze | first6 = T. | doi = 10.1016/j.marpol.2009.12.004 | title = Decision bias in marine spatial planning of offshore wind farms: Problems of singular versus cumulative assessments of economic impacts on fisheries | journal = Marine Policy | volume = 34 | issue = 3 | pages = 733 | year = 2010 | pmid = | pmc = }}</ref> and will cost over €1 billion to construct once fully operational (€900m for phase I alone). Originally known as '''Borkum West II''' the name was changed to '''Trianel Windpark Borkum''' in early 2013.
Phase 1 of the installation was completed in the 4th quarter of 2014 and consist of 40 Areva M5000-116 turbines (5&nbsp;MW turbines) on [[Tripod (foundation)|Tripod foundations]].<ref name=trianel>{{cite web|url=http://www.trianel-borkum.de/en/wind-farm/facts-and-figures.html |title= Facts and figures |website= trianel-borkum.de |accessdate=17 August 2013}}</ref> It was connected to the grid in August 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.renewablesinternational.net/germany-adds-lots-of-offshore-wind/150/435/89907/|title=Germany adds lots of offshore wind|publisher=}}</ref> In the six months before March 2016 the wind farm produced 452.33&nbsp;[[GWh]],<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.presseportal.de/pm/67884/3280198 |title= Trianel Windpark Borkum halbes Jahr in Betrieb Erster rein kommunaler Offshore-Windpark erfüllt positive Erwartungen |website= presseportal.de |date= 2016-03-18 |accessdate= 2017-03-05 |language= de |trans-title=Trianel Windpark Borkum half year in operation First purely municipal offshore wind farm fulfills positive expectations}}</ref> i.e. a [[capacity factor]] of 51.6%<!-- 452,330 MWh/ (1/2 year) / ( 200 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.516 -->.
In September 2016 [[Senvion]] was awarded a conditional contract for the second phase, for 32 upgraded 6.2M152 turbines rated at a total power of 203&nbsp;MW. A final investment decision is expected in the first half of 2017 after which construction could start in early 2018 for a planned completion in the fall of 2019.<ref name=trianel2>{{cite web|url= https://www.trianel.com/pm/trianel-windpark-borkum-ii-count-on-senvion-offshore-turbines/ |title= Trianel Windpark Borkum II counts on Senvion offshore turbines |website= trianel.com |date= 2016-09-28 |accessdate= 2017-03-05}}</ref> ==References== {{Reflist}}
